To assess the impact of long COVID on each outcome, the attributable fraction or etiological fraction (EF) was calculated only for the dichotomized long COVID responses. This measure elicits the maximum reduction in the use of services if long COVID is eliminated. The EF was calculated as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\text{EF }} = \, \left[ {{\text{PO}}*\left( {{\text{PR}}{-}{1}.0} \right)} \right]/{1} + [\left( {{\text{PO}}*\left( {{\text{PR}} - {1}} \right)} \right]$$\end{document}EF=PO∗PR-1.0/1+[PO∗PR-1where, PO = prevalence of the outcome; PR = crude prevalence ratio.
